</p>
<p>Ok, try this out one more time.</p>
<p>It should be slow the first time... yes! And then super fast the second time. In
the terminal, we can even see a <code>/tmp/doctrine_cache/</code> directory:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">ls /tmp/doctrine_cache/</div></code></pre>
<p>Big picture time: bundles give you services, and those services can be controlled
in <code>config.yml</code>. Every bundle works a little bit different - but if you understand
this basic concept, you're on your way.</p>

    
